==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Post-disseizin
<hw>Post"-dis*sei"zin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>post-</ets> + <ets>disseizin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>A subsequent disseizin committed by one of lands which the
disseizee had before recovered of the same disseizor; a writ founded on
such subsequent disseizin, now abolished.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.
Tomlins.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Post-disseizor</ent>⟦br⟧
